[SN]TITLE[SN]
Crom Castle: Man in hospital after roof rescue

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been taken to hospital by helicopter after being rescued from a roof at Crom Castle in Newtownbutler, County Fermanagh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Northern Ireland Fire and Rescue Service said two fire engines attended the scene "of a man believed to have fallen from a roof on the fourth floor of a building in the area".
The incident happened on Monday afternoon.
The man was taken to a nearby hospital for treatment to his injuries.
